pr_title: Setup check and added test examples
pr_body: Added jibx-maven-plugins and dependencies for setup.
pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 433413403, 'comment_body': 'I would add the .idea, .classpath, .project, .settings, and .ant-target-build.xml to the gitignore since these are IDE specific.  When we complete the project, it should be able to run just using the maven commands from the command lines.  @rtgdk let me know if you disagree.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 1, 18, 31, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'goneall', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 433416480, 'comment_body': 'This should be a directory local to the project (e.g. a src/main/config)  You can put the schema in the local directory. pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 484100546, 'comment_body': "We should remove the entire method - not just the declaration.  You can't delete the method inside the for loop, so you'll need to create an array list `List<MethodDeclaration> methodsToBeDeleted ...` prior to the `for (MethodDeclaration md...` and add to that list when you find any setMethod that has a List as a parameter.    You can loop through the `methodsToBeDeleted` after the `for (MethodDeclaration md...` and call the `delete()` function - similar to the approach for removing `typeArgument`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 9, 6, 18, 30, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'goneall', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 484100591, 'comment_body': "This method should be removed - we don't want any setters for lists - only the getters", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 9, 6, 18, 31, 26, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'goneall', 'type': 'User'}]
